// The "extra" section contains the EAS project ID for building and submitting the app.
// The "experiments" section enables typed routes in the Expo Router.
// The "android" and "ios" sections specify platform-specific configurations, such as package names and tablet support.
// The "web" section configures the web bundler and output settings, including the favicon.
// The "version" field indicates the current version of the app, which is set to "1.0.0".
// The "orientation" is set to "portrait", and the "userInterfaceStyle" is set to "automatic" to adapt to the user's preferences.
// The "icon" and "adaptiveIcon" fields specify the app's icons for different platforms.
// The "scheme" field defines a custom URL scheme for the app, allowing it to be opened via links with the "mobileapp" scheme.
// The "supportsTablet" field indicates that the iOS version of the app supports tablet devices.
// The "output" field in the "web" section specifies that the web app will be built using the Metro bundler and output as static files.
// The "favicon" field specifies the favicon for the web app, which is used in browser tabs and bookmarks.
